---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '9 April 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | FisherDigital"
  description="Terms of service for FisherDigital website design and AI services. Covers payments, intellectual property, and what to expect when working with us."
  schemaType="legal"
>
  <section class="section-light py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">

      <!-- Header -->
      <p class="label mb-4">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-4">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-12">
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-base leading-relaxed">

        <!-- Intro -->
        <div>
          <p>
            These terms apply when you use the FisherDigital website (fisherdigital.co.uk) or
            engage us for web design, AI integration, or related services. By using our site
            or hiring us, you agree to these terms.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            If anything here is unclear, just ask. We would rather have a quick conversation than
            leave you guessing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Who we are -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Who we are</h2>
          <p>
            FisherDigital is a web design studio operated by Joshua Fisher, based in Bristol, United Kingdom.
            When these terms say "we", "us", or "our", they mean FisherDigital.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Services -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Services we provide</h2>
          <p>
            We design and build websites for local businesses. Depending on the plan you choose,
            this may also include AI chatbot setup, AI receptionist integration, booking systems,
            search engine optimisation, and ongoing hosting and support.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The exact scope of work is agreed before any payment is taken. We will always walk you
            through a live demo of your site before asking for payment.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quotes and pricing -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Quotes and pricing</h2>
          <p>
            All prices on our website are listed in British Pounds (GBP) and are indicative starting
            prices. Your final quote depends on the specific requirements of your project.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            A quote is valid for 30 days from the date we send it. After that, we may need to revise
            it if circumstances have changed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Payment -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Payment</h2>
          <p>
            Payments are processed securely through Stripe. We accept major debit and credit cards.
            All transactions are in GBP.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            For one-off website builds, we typically collect payment after you have seen and approved
            your live demo. For plans that include monthly hosting and support, the monthly fee begins
            once your site goes live.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            If a payment fails or is disputed, we will contact you to resolve it before taking any
            action on your site.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- What you provide -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">What we need from you</h2>
          <p>
            To build your site, we may need things like your business name, logo, photos, copy,
            and contact details. You are responsible for making sure you have the right to use any
            content you provide to us.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Delays in providing materials may push back your project timeline. We will always
            keep you updated if this happens.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- IP -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Intellectual property</h2>
          <p>
            Once your project is paid in full, you own the final website we build for you. That includes
            the design, layout, and any custom content we create specifically for your business.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We retain ownership of any reusable templates, code libraries, tools, and processes
            that we use across multiple client projects. These are not unique to your site and
            existed before or independently of your project.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We may feature your completed site in our portfolio unless you ask us not to.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Third party services -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Third-party services</h2>
          <p>
            Your website may use third-party tools such as Google Analytics, Formspree, or AI
            service providers. These services have their own terms and privacy policies. We will
            let you know which services are used on your site.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We are not responsible for downtime, changes, or issues caused by third-party services
            outside our control.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Liability -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p>
            We work hard to deliver quality results, but we cannot guarantee specific business outcomes
            like increased sales, enquiries, or search rankings. Websites are one part of a bigger picture.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, our total liability for any claim arising from
            our services is limited to the amount you paid us for the specific project in question.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We are not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential losses, including lost
            profits, data loss, or business interruption.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Nothing in these terms limits our liability for fraud, death or personal injury caused
            by our negligence, or any other liability that cannot be excluded by law.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Cancellation -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Cancellation</h2>
          <p>
            If you decide not to go ahead before your site goes live, that is fine. Since we build
            your demo before taking payment, there is usually nothing to refund.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            For monthly plans, you can cancel at any time. Your site will remain live until the end
            of your current billing period.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Website use -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Using this website</h2>
          <p>
            You may browse fisherdigital.co.uk freely. Please do not attempt to interfere with the
            site's operation, scrape its content in bulk, or use it for any unlawful purpose.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            All content on this site, including text, images, and design, is owned by FisherDigital
            unless otherwise stated. You may not reproduce it without permission.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Changes -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Changes to these terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these terms from time to time. When we do, we will update the "last updated"
            date at the top. Continued use of our website or services after changes are posted means
            you accept the updated terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Governing law -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Governing law</h2>
          <p>
            These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes will be subject
            to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <div class="pt-6 border-t border-border">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Get in touch</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about these terms, contact us at:
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4 text-text-secondary">
            <p>FisherDigital</p>
            <p>Bristol, United Kingdom</p>
            <p>
              <a href="mailto:fisherwebco@gmail.com" class="text-accent hover:underline">fisherwebco@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
